n><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533450\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104woq1665702862912.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/woq1665702862912.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/woq1665702862912.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"woq1665702862912\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Generating HTML class Attributes for Styling\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The HTML generated by Uniface for dynamic server page components includes HTML attributes for formatting the layout. These attributes are determined by declaratively-defined widget definitions, dynamically-set properties, and HTML attributes explicitly defined in the server page layout.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"woq1665702862912__p_d21308e1_d21309e1_d21310e1\">HTML elements are more commonly styled using Cascading Style Sheets, which apply a set of properties to the element based on the value of its class attribute. The <code class=\"ph codeph\">class</code> attribute may specify multiple classes.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"woq1665702862912__p_d21311e1_d21312e1_d21313e1\">Uniface automatically generates elements with custom <code class=\"ph codeph\">class</code> attributes for:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"woq1665702862912__li_d10373e1_d10374e1_d10375e1\">Bound syntax errors. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aqh1665702590886.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqh1665702590886.html\" title=\"Uniface always performs server-side syntax checks when data in a dynamic server page (DSP) is validated or stored. It is also possible to perform browser-side syntax checks, so that errors are flagged before incorrect data is submitted to the server.\">Syntax Checking in Dynamic Server Pages</a>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"woq1665702862912__li_d10376e1_d10377e1_d10378e1\">Empty entity and occurrence elements. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cks1665702588253.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cks1665702588253.html\" title=\"When Uniface generates HTML for dynamic server pages (DSPs), it sets HTML class attributes that can be used to style the server page.\">Styling Entities and Occurrences in HTML</a>.\n                        </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"woq1665702862912__li_d10379e1_d10380e1_d10381e1\">Mobile app layouts defined by the <code class=\"ph codeph\">data-uniface-role</code> attribute. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wun1665702755914.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wun1665702755914.html\" title=\"Each mobile platform has its own user interface and interaction conventions, which affect the layout of a mobile application. The Mobile App Layout is a framework that maps HTML elements in a DSP layout to generic layout definitions.\">Mobile App Layout</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sms1665702756004.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sms1665702756004.html\" title=\"Custom attribute that is applied to an element in the HTML layout of a Dynamic Server Page component to bind it to a definition in the Mobile App Layout framework.\">data-uniface-role</a>.\n                        </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"woq1665702862912__p_d21314e1_d21315e1_d21316e1\">You can use Uniface's class attributes to apply your own styles. For example, you could suppress empty occurrences or display errors based on the class applied to the element. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">&lt;style media=\"screen\" type=\"text/css\"&gt;\n .-uocc-empty- {\n display: none; \n }\n&lt;/style&gt; </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"woq1665702862912__p_d21317e1_d21318e1_d21319e1\">In addition to Uniface's own classes, you can instruct Uniface to add your own styles to any element bound to a Uniface object. To do so, you can set the <code class=\"ph codeph\">class:<var class=\"keyword varname\">ClassName</var>\n</code> widget property. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fjp1665702589680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fjp1665702589680.html\" title=\"The name of a class to be dynamically added to (or removed from) the list of classes specified by the class attribute of a bound HTML element.\">class:ClassName</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533450\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533450\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Generating HTML class Attributes for Styling Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Generating HTML class Attributes for Styling The HTML generated by Uniface for dynamic server page components includes HTML attributes for formatting the layout. These attributes are determined by declaratively-defined widget definitions, dynamically-set properties, and HTML attributes explicitly defined in the server page layout. HTML elements are more commonly styled using Cascading Style Sheets, which apply a set of properties to the element based on the value of its class attribute. The class attribute may specify multiple classes. Uniface automatically generates elements with custom class attributes for: Bound syntax errors. For more information, see Syntax Checking in Dynamic Server Pages . Empty entity and occurrence elements. For more information, see Styling Entities and Occurrences in HTML . Mobile app layouts defined by the data-uniface-role attribute. For more information, see Mobile App Layout and data-uniface-role . You can use Uniface's class attributes to apply your own styles. For example, you could suppress empty occurrences or display errors based on the class applied to the element. For example: <style media=\"screen\" type=\"text/css\"> .-uocc-empty- { display: none; } </style> Copy In addition to Uniface's own classes, you can instruct Uniface to add your own styles to any element bound to a Uniface object. To do so, you can set the class: ClassName widget property. For more information, see class:ClassName . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}